{{Infobox central bank | native_name = Banka Ya Botswana | executive = [[Moses Dinekere Pelaelo]] | executive_title = Governor | established = {{Start date|1975|7|1|df=y}} | headquarters = [[Gaborone]], [[Botswana]] | bank_of = [[Botswana]] | currency = [[Botswana pula]] | currency_iso = BWP | borrowing_rate = 5.5% | deposit_rate = | website = [http://www.bankofbotswana.bw/ bankofbotswana.bw] | footnotes = }} The '''Bank of Botswana''' ('''BoB''') is the [[central bank]] of [[Botswana]].
When Botswana gained independence from Britain in 1966, the country was part of the [[Common Monetary Area|Rand Monetary Area]] (RMA). In 1974 Botswana withdrew from the RMA, and the Bank of Botswana and Financial Institution Acts established the legal framework for a central bank in Botswana to be established in 1975. The [[Botswana pula|pula]] was launched as a national currency in 1976, and in 1977 the Bank of Botswana became the government banker.<ref>{{cite book|first=Fred|last=Morton|first2=Jeff|last2=Ramsay|first3=Part Themba|last3=Mgadla|title=Historical Dictionary of Botswana|series=African Historical Dictionaries|volume=108|location=Metuchen, New Jersey|publisher=Scarecrow Press|edition=4th|year=2008|isbn=978-0-8108-5467-3|contribution=Bank of Botswana (BoB)|pages=40}}</ref>
