The '''Barák Workers Association''' ({{lang-de|Arbeitervereinigung Barák}}) was a [[Czech people|Czech]] educational organization in Austria during the [[interbellum]] years. The association was linked to the [[Czech National Social Party|Czech National Socialist Party]], and was an important pillar of the party in Austria.<ref>Brousek, Karl M. ''[https://books.google.com/books?hl=sv&id=U1yMS8ozHOoC Wien und seine Tschechen: Integration und Assimilation einer Minderheit im 20. Jahrhundert]''. Schriftenreihe des Österreichischen Ost- und Südosteuropa-Instituts, Bd. 7. München: Oldenbourg, 1980. p. 75</ref>

