The '''Democratic Rally of the Comoros''' ({{lang-fr|Rassemblement Démocratique des Comores}}, RDC) is a political party in the [[Comoros]] led by [[Mouigni Baraka]], Governor of [[Grande Comore]].

==History==
The party was established in November 2013.<ref>Tom Lansford (2015) ''Political Handbook of the World 2015'', CQ Press</ref> In the [[Comorian legislative election, 2015|2015 parliamentary elections]] the RDC won two of the 24 directly-elected seats;<ref>[http://www.comores-actualites.com/non-classe/comores-elections-resultats-de-la-ceni-pour-le-2eme-tour/ Comorian elections: CENI results for the second round!] Comores Actualités, 26 February 2015 {{fr icon}}</ref> [[Oumouri Hadjira]] was elected in [[Itsahidi]] and [[M'madi Hassani Oumouri]] in [[Itsandra]] North.<ref>[http://www.cenicomores.km/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/R%C3%A9sultats-2%C3%A8me-tour-par-Bureaux-de-Vote.pdf Résultats du 2ème tour des élections de Représentants de la Nation 2015] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402122406/http://www.cenicomores.km/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/R%C3%A9sultats-2%C3%A8me-tour-par-Bureaux-de-Vote.pdf |date=2015-04-02 }} CENI {{fr icon}}</ref>

