{{Infobox Internet exchange point | name = Finnish Communication and Internet Exchange | image = [[File:FICIX logo blue.svg]] | full_name = Finnish Communication and Internet Exchange | abbreviation = FICIX | founded = 1993 | location = {{FIN}} | members = 29 (2017)<ref>https://www.ficix.fi/info/</ref> | ports = | website = {{Url|https://www.ficix.fi/}} | peak = | peak_in = | peak_out = | daily = | daily_in = | daily_out = }}
'''Finnish Communication and Internet Exchange – FICIX ry''' is the first and the biggest [[Internet exchange point]] in [[Finland]]. As of 2009, FICIX consists of three exchange points.
FICIX was founded in 1993 and was originally called the "Finnish Commercial Internet Exchange". The name was changed to the current form in 2001, when a non-profit organization was founded to maintain operations.
FICIX-1 is located in [[Otaniemi]], [[Espoo]]. Established in 1999, FICIX-2 is located in [[Pasila]], [[Helsinki]]. FICIX-3 is located in [[Oulu]] and was established in March 2008.<ref>[http://hightechforum.kaleva.fi/index.cfm?alue=10&Id1=721655&OpenStory=1&lang=1 HighTech Forum – Ouluun uusi ip-yhdysliikennepiste<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071129225307/http://hightechforum.kaleva.fi/index.cfm?alue=10 |date=2007-11-29 }}</ref> FICIX also operates the three [[root nameserver]]s located in Finland, I (in Espoo), K (in Helsinki), and J (in Oulu).<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ficix.fi/tiedotteet/tiedote-080407.txt | title = Ouluun uusi IP-yhdysliikennepiste ja juurinimipalvelin | language = Finnish | date = 2008-04-07 | accessdate = 2009-01-21 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090513045910/http://www.ficix.fi/tiedotteet/tiedote-080407.txt | archivedate = 2009-05-13 | df = }}</ref>
