{{Expand French|Cavalcade de Scaër|date=April 2014}} {{Infobox recurring event | name = Cavalcade of Scaër | native_name = Cavalcade de Scaër | logo = | logo_caption = | image = Ganeshzoskuizh.jpg | caption = A [[Float (parade)|float]] during The Cavalcade in 2007 | status = active | genre = [[Carnival]] | date = <!--"dates=" also works, but do not use both--> | begins = {{Date|2014-05-24|df=y}} | ends = {{Date|2014-05-25|df=y}} | frequency = Annually | venue = | location = [[Scaër]] | coordinates = {{Coord|48.0281|-3.7008|region:FR_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = [[France]] | years_active = {{#expr:{{CURRENTYEAR}}-1923-5}} | first = {{Start date|1923|05<!--|DD|df=y-->}} | founder_name = | last = {{End date|2013|05|19|df=y}} – {{End date|2013|05|20|df=y}} | prev = | next = | participants = | attendance = 50,000 | area = | budget = | patron = | organised = <!--"organized=" also works--> | filing = <!-- Filing status --> | people = | member = | website = {{URL|http://lacavalcade.fr/|link}} | footnotes = }} '''The Cavalcade of Scaër''' ({{lang-fr|La Cavalcade de Scaër}}; or '''The Cavalcade''') is a [[carnival]] festival that takes place in the town of [[Scaër]], a [[Communes of France|commune]] in the [[Finistère]] [[Departments of France|department]] of [[Brittany (administrative region)|Brittany]] in northwestern [[France]]. Every odd year since 1923, during the [[Pentecost]] weekend (Sunday and Monday), about 5,000 inhabitants of Scaër welcome about 50,000 spectators for The Cavalcade carnival, which the town owes its nickname {{lang-fr|"Scaër la Joyeuse"}} ("Scaër the Merry").
